<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   No Differences With U.S. on Mideast Settlement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    No Differences With U.S. on Mideast Settlement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2704140094 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0900 GMT 
27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2704140094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russia and the United States now have no fundamental 
differences on problems of an Arab-Israeli settlement, Russia's 
Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev stated after his meeting in 
Geneva with U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher. In the 
past week Moscow was the center of the Middle East peace 
process, he said: it was visited by PLO leader Yasir `Arafat and 
Israel's Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin. Now Washington is, as it 
were, taking over the baton from us, and it is very important 
for our actions to be coordinated, Kozyrev stressed. The 
Russian minister had in mind the visit by the U.S. Secretary of 
State to the Near East, which starts today. Christopher will 
visit Saudi Arabia, Egypt, Israel and Syria. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

