<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Israeli Prime Minister Wraps Up Visit to Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Israeli Prime Minister Wraps Up Visit to Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Rabin Condemns Hamas </H4>

<F P=102> LD2604172194 Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy in Russian 
1500 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2604172194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today, Yitzhaq Rabin told a group of journalists in 
Moscow that there continues to be a major chance of implementing 
the Near East peace process. Yitzhaq Rabin noted: 
  [Begin Rabin recording, in Hebrew, with superimposed Russian 
translation] At all events there is no doubt that public support 
for the peace process and agreement with the PLO [brief break in 
transmission] a consequence of certain political views. This is 
the natural result of the disillusionment of very many of our 
people. People are disappointed that, while the talks seem to 
be continuing, the number of terrorist acts is not only not 
declining but, in terms of the number of casualties...[pauses] 
More and more people are suffering. This is a direct result of 
the fact that Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] and the 
Islamic Jihad, which are responsible for this terror, are headed 
by extremists and religious fanatics, who will go to any lengths 
to strangle the peace process. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

