<H3> <TI>   Israeli Prime Minister Wraps Up Visit to Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Israeli Prime Minister Wraps Up Visit to Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Rabin, Chernomyrdin Sign Trade Accord </H4>

<F P=102> LD2704140594 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1300 GMT 
27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2704140594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] This morning at the capital's airport Vnukovo-II, 
Viktor Chernomyrdin and Israel's Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin 
signed a trade and economic agreement. It lays the legal basis 
for large-scale Russian-Israeli economic cooperation. 
  Interfax reports that the the idea for signing such a 
document had arisen in the course of intergovernmental talks in 
Moscow on 25 April. The agreement was prepared in the course of 
24 hours. After the signing of the trade and economic 
agreement, the head of the Israeli Government set off for St. 
Petersburg. 

</TEXT>

