<H3> <TI>   Russian Delegation Holds Talks in Damascus </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Delegation Holds Talks in Damascus </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Soskovets Meets Syrian Defense Minister </H4>

<F P=102> LD2604161194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1422 
GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2604161194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS special correspondent Oleg Velichko] </F>
  [Text] Damascus, 26 Apr -- Oleg Soskovets, first deputy 
chairman of the Russian Federation Government, who is on an 
official visit to Syria, today held talks with General Mustafa 
Talas, the Syrian deputy prime minister and minister of defense. 
  Yuriy Mikhaylov, the vice premier's advisor, told an 
ITAR-TASS correspondent that the prospects for bilateral 
cooperation were examined at the meeting. During the talks Oleg 
Soskovets noted that Russia continues to view Syria as a 
friendly state. "We must not waste all that we have achieved 
before in our relations," he said. "We have been friends for too 
long." 
  Mustafa Talas supported the position of the Russian first 
vice premier. Nevertheless, the general noted a certain cooling 
in mutual relations between the two states, particularly in the 
last few years. He spoke of Syria's readiness to open a new 
page in cooperation with Russia. 
  Oleg Soskovets described the agreement on cooperation 
between 
our two countries, which is being prepared for signing within 
the framework of the Russian delegation's visit, as first and 
foremost a political step. "The position of the Russian 
leadership is clear -- to enter into normal cooperation," he 
stressed. 

</TEXT>

