<H3> <TI>   Russian Delegation Holds Talks in Damascus </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Delegation Holds Talks in Damascus </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Military Cooperation Agreement Signed </H4>

<F P=102> LD2704194394 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1857 
GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2704194394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Dmitriy Zelenin and Oleg </F>
Velichko] 
  [Text] Damascus, 27 Apr -- Oleg Soskovets, Russian first 
deputy prime minister, who is here on an official visit, and 
Syrian Defense Minister Mustafa Talas, today signed an agreement 
on military-technical cooperation. 
  After the signing of the document, the Russian first deputy 
prime minister said that the Russian president considers it 
essential to resume cooperation between the two states that has 
been partially lost of late. The signing of today's agreement, 
Oleg Soskovets noted, shows the desire of Moscow and Syria to 
engage in systematic cooperation in the military-technical 
sphere. 
  Mustafa Talas appraised the agreement as "a first step in 
the 
right direction." He expressed the need for a restoration of 
the former relationship with Russia. In this respect, he 
particularly emphasized that Damascus "has strong friends in 
Moscow." "The agreement signed today is evidence of this," he 
said. 
  As for the essence of the document, an ITAR-TASS 
correspondent was told by a well-informed source in the Russian 
delegation that it is evidence of the beginning of a new 
relationship. The two sides agreed to form a working 
commission, which will set about its work in a few weeks' time. 
  Today, too, Oleg Soskovets had a three-hour meeting with 
Syrian President Hafiz al-Asad. According to the deputy prime 
minister, the Syrian head of state supported the main positions 
in the agreement on military-technical cooperation. 
  After the signing of the agreement, Oleg Soskovets left by 
air for Moscow. 

</TEXT>

