<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Delegation Holds Talks in Damascus </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    No `Offensive' Arms To Be Sold </H4>

<F P=102> MK2804071094 Moscow SEGODNYA in Russian 28 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> MK2804071094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow SEGODNYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Russia Will Sell to Syria `Only </F>
Defense Weapons'"] 
  [Text] Boris Kolokolov, Russian Federation deputy foreign 
minister, has stated that Russia will not sell offensive weapons 
to Syria. "The question now is only the selling of spare parts 
for weapons delivered earlier. We can only speak about the 
deliveries to Syria of spare parts and `defense weapons,'" he 
said. He also pointed out that Russia would give Tel Aviv 
"whatever help it can" in looking for Israeli soldiers taken 
prisoner or missing in action: "Oleg Soskovets, who is on a 
visit to Damascus, has already been instructed correspondingly," 
Mr. Kolokolov said. 

</TEXT>

