<F P=102>   LD2804084294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0823 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2804084294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Vladimir Solntsev] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 28 TASS -- The Russian Foreign Ministry 
positively appraised the appointment of Koji Kakizawa on 
Thursday to the post of Japanese foreign minister. 
  A high-ranking representative of the Russian Foreign Office 
noted in an interview with ITAR-TASS that Kakizawa "was long 
known as a man who actively participated in implementing 
Japanese foreign policy in many spheres, including the problem 
of ensuring security and settlement in Cambodia. 
  As for relations with Russia, the diplomat noted, "We 
proceed 
from a premise that they will constructively develop in the 
spirit of the positive tenor which is characteristic of the 
bilateral dialogue after the Tokyo visit by President Boris 
Yeltsin last October". 
  Kakizawa who was parliamentary deputy of the Japanese 
foreign 
minister in the past, repeatedly pointed to the need for 
"serious efforts to establish closer and normal relations 
between Japan and such important neighbour as the Russian 
Federation", stressing that these should be "long-term relations 
of friendship" turned to the 21st Century. 

