<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Latvian, Russian Experts Discuss Troop Withdrawal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Latvian, Russian Experts Discuss Troop Withdrawal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2604120294 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0651 
GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2604120294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Kuchina] </F>
  [Text] Jurmala, 26 Apr -- Groups of experts from the two 
countries' delegations started work in Jurmala today within the 
framework of the preparations for the meeting of the presidents 
of Latvia and Russia. Sergey Zotov, head of the Russian 
delegation, noted that amendments cannot be made to the already 
initialled package of agreements, which consists of four 
documents. However, the interests of the Latvian side will 
possibly be taken into account during discussion of the 
mechanism for implementing individual points. 
  Reaffirming Russia's willingness to withdraw its troops from 
Latvia by 31 August, Zotov stressed that only the signing of the 
entire package of documents relating to the withdrawal of the 
army units would be acceptable to Russia. 
  In his turn Guntis Ulmanis, as was reported at his office, 
is 
insisting on the introduction of substantial corrections into 
the agreement on social protection for military pensioners 
resident in Latvia. Today representatives of the foreign policy 
departments of the two countries will set the date in Moscow for 
the meeting with President Yeltsin. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

