<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baku (April 26) TURAN -- This evening the CSCE Minsk 
Group on Nagorno Karabakh headed by the Swedish diplomat, 
Mathias Mosberg, will visit Baku for a day. 
  The delegation consists of 14 people, which includes 
military 
experts and diplomats. The delegation will meet with the 
Azerbaijani leadership and will visit the front line. Earlier 
when Geydar Aliyev met with the Turkish Foreign Minister Hikmet 
Cetin, he called upon the CSCE to take an active part in the 
peace settlement of the Azeri-Armenian conflict. 

