<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Li Peng Thanks Nazarbayev for Realistic Approach </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Peng Thanks Nazarbayev for Realistic Approach </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2604175694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1634 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2604175694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] During his talks with the leadership of Kazakhstan 
the Premier of the Chinese State Council Li Peng thanked 
President Nursultan Nazarbayev for a balanced and realistic 
approach to all aspects of bilateral relations. This was 
disclosed at a Tuesday briefing in Alma-Ata [Almaty] by a 
spokesman for the Chinese Foreign Ministry. 
  He said Nazarbayev is not letting Eastern Turkestan, an 
organization of separatists from several Central Asian countries 
claiming territories in North China, to engage in subversive 
activities against China from Kazakhstan. The Kazakh leader 
also views Taiwan as an inseparable part of China. 
  The spokesman said that the calls made at a Tuesday rally in 
Alma-Ata organized by the Nevada-Semipalatinsk movement and 
Eastern Turkestan to stop nuclear tests at Lobnor test ground 
are senseless because no nuclear tests are conducted there. 
  The official said Li Peng invited Nazarbayev to visit China 
at a time suitable for him for the final settlement of remaining 
border problems. 

</TEXT>

