<HT>    "drsov082_t_94003" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-082 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  26 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> BALTIC STATES </F>
<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Commission To Supervise Removal of Nuclear Fuel </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Commission To Supervise Removal of Nuclear Fuel </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2604165194 Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network in Estonian 1600 
GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2604165194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network </F>
<F P=105>  Estonian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The government formed a high-level commission today 
to monitor and regulate the removal of Russian nuclear reactors 
from the Paldiski naval base near Tallinn. The commission will 
be led by Energy Minister Arvo Niitenberg. Other members 
include Foreign Minister Juri Luik, Interior Minister Heiki 
Arike, and Environment Minister Andres Tarand. Premier Mart 
Laar said that the ministers appointed as members will also be 
able appropriate representatives and specialists from any 
relevant department as needed. 
  (?Estonia) has stated repeatedly that it is ready for the 
nuclear fuel removal and the dismantlement of the nuclear 
reactors. Estonia will impose a special regime on Pakri 
peninsula for the time of the nuclear fuel removal, as the 
Estonian side must ensure safety of this procedure. According 
to preliminary information the removal of nuclear fuel will 
begin in early May. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

