<F P=106> [From the "Slavyanka" program of the Russian Defense </F>
Ministry] 
  [Text] The press center of the Volga Military District has 
announced that in the Sorskiy garrison of the district there was 
a working meeting of the officers of the peacekeeping forces of 
Russia and the United States. 
  For three days, experts from the staffs of the Russian 27th 
Motorized Infantry Division and the 3d Infantry Division of the 
United States completed work on the plan for the joint 
command-staff exercise of the peacekeeping forces to be held 
from 4 to 14 July. Summing up the results of the working 
meeting, Major-General Anatoliy Sidyagin, head of the exercises 
on the Russian side, highly appraised the level of professional 
training of the Russian and American peacekeepers. 

