<H3> <TI>   `No Obstacles' to Russian Army Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `No Obstacles' to Russian Army Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2804173994 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1600 GMT 28 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2804173994 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>
<F P=105>  Latvian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today in Jurmala, groups of experts of the Latvian- 
Russian interstate talks completed the coordination of an 
additional protocol to the agreement on social guarantees for 
the discharged Russian military that was submitted by Latvia. 
With this, there are no obstacles now to the delegations 
signing the package of documents on the withdrawal of the 
Russian Army, Sergey Zotov, head of the Russian delegation, 
believes. 
  Aivars Vovers, deputy head of the Latvian delegation, also 
admitted that there are no obstacles now for a meeting between 
the Latvian and Russian presidents, from the point of view of 
the readiness of the agreements. The protocol provides for 
several ways to tackle the issues related to emigration to 
Russia or other states by the Russian officers discharged in 
Latvia, if they wish to do so. 
  It is envisaged to tackle the issue of the amount of payment 
for rent of the Skrunda radar station at the presidents' 
meeting. 

</TEXT>

