BFN 

<F P=106> [From 29 April PREVALEHT, p.3; "News Bulletin" No. 82/94] </F>
  [Text] The peacekeeping company currently being formed in 
Estonia will be ready to participate in the international 
peacekeeping forces joint exercise in the Netherlands this 
autumn, General Aleksander Einseln told the NACC [North Atlantic 
Cooperation Council] session yesterday. 
  General Einseln has prepared a draft resolution on the 
forming of an independent peacekeeping infantry company and 
submitted it to the government. The Defence Ministry will have 
to prepare the budget and the listing of personnel for the 
company. 
  The Foreign Ministry announced that the definite plan for 
Estonia's participation in the "Partnership for Peace" NATO 
cooperation programme will be completed by mid-May. The 
military resources to be turned over under NATO control need to 
be elaborated still. The government will have to approve the 
budget of the programme after which the plan will be submitted 
to NATO HQ. 

