<H3> <TI>   New Faction Registered at State Duma </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Faction Registered at State Duma </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2804161294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1256 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2804161294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Pavel Kuznetsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 28 TASS -- The Russian State Duma 
registered a new deputy faction on Thursday, the Liberal 
Democratic Union "December 12." 
  The faction will have its own office and representatives in 
the Duma Council. 
  Under the regulations adopted by the Duma a parliamentary 
faction has to have at least 35 members to be officially 
registered. The new faction has 39 deputies, including former 
members of the reformist Russia's Choice bloc and the 
nationalist Liberal Democratic Party of Russia. 

</TEXT>

