BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tamara Zamyatina] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 29 TASS -- Reinforced police squads 
will patrol Moscow streets during the May Day celebrations, 
taking into account the last year's deplorable experience, 
Moscow Mayor Yuriy Luzhkov said in an interview with ITAR-TASS 
here on Friday. 
  According to the mayor, he is more worried over "terrorist 
acts rather than organised actions by gunmen". Luzhkov stressed 
that "no matter how the situation changes in the capital, the 
townhall is fully prepared to counter extremists". 
  The Moscow mayor plans to spend all four off-days at his 
office. 

