<F P=102>   PM2804162994 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> PM2804162994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Untitled POSTFACTUM report from the "Events of the Week" </F>
roundup -- from the FINANSOVYYE IZVESTIYA section page I] 
  [Text] The Russian Government owes Moscow 126 billion 
rubles [R]. The failure to pay this money is creating problems 
for the Moscow Government in paying wages to workers in 
budget-funded organizations and financing subway construction. 
A few days ago Moscow Mayor Yuriy Luzhkov noted that Moscow is 
honoring its commitments to the federal budget impeccably, 
adding that it would be more correct if the city were allowed to 
retain part of the taxes for itself "instead of transferring 
them to the federal budget and then waiting for money to come 
back." Luzhkov asked the tax services to examine this option 
for collaborating with the federal authorities in the budget 
sphere. 

</TEXT>

