<H3> <TI>   Tatarstan Opposition Sets Up Anti-Bureaucratic Front </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tatarstan Opposition Sets Up Anti-Bureaucratic Front </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK2804130094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 28 Apr 94 
p 3 </F>

<F P=103> MK2804130094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report under the "NEGA Reports" rubric: </F>
"Tatarstan"] 
  [Text] Leaders of four public organizations -- the Tatar 
Public Center, the Tatarstan Communist Party, the Republican 
Party of Tatarstan, and the People's Front of Tatarstan -- have 
announced the creation of a new democratic opposition 
organization, the Anti-Bureaucratic Front of Tatarstan [AFT]. 
The front stands for the resignation of the bankrupt Sabirov 
government, cuts in and the reorganization of the government 
staff, a merger of the presidential staff with that of the 
Cabinet of Ministers, the abolition of the posts of vice 
president and deputy prime ministers, election of all 
administration chiefs, open decisionmaking by the government (no 
secrets from the people), the publication of all secret 
agreements, the freedom of the mass media, and demands that 
every step, every decision, and every thought of bureaucracy be 
placed under people's control. 

</TEXT>

