<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Border Crossing With PRC To Open in Maritime Kray </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Border Crossing With PRC To Open in Maritime Kray </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2904005594 Vladivostok Radiostantsiya Tikhiy Okean 
Maritime Network in Russian 0715 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2904005594 </F>
<F P=104>  Vladivostok Radiostantsiya Tikhiy Okean 
Maritime Network </F>

<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Pacific Ocean" Program] </F>
  [Text] Another border crossing will be added to the two 
existing major cargo and passenger crossings at Grodekova and 
Poltavka in the Maritime Kray. The crossing, to be opened at 
Turiy Rog settlement in Khankayskiy Rayon, will establish the 
shortest route to the Chinese city of Mishan for thousands of 
tourists and businessmen. 
  The traffic capacity of the new point will be comparatively 
small -- four tourist groups per day. However, according to 
Aleksandr Berestavov, chairman of the Kray Committee for 
Tourism, the opening of motor vehicle access across the border 
will make it easier for many Russians to become acquainted with 
China. 
  In turn, tourists from China, whose numbers have risen 
sharply with the introduction of visa-less exchanges of tourists 
between the two countries, now have one more window into 
Russia's Far East. 

</TEXT>

