<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Filatov Addresses Conference on CIS Economic Space </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Filatov Addresses Conference on CIS Economic Space </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2604131894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0757 
GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2604131894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Yezhov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 26 Apr -- Trends in the development of the 
CIS clearly show that processes within the CIS member states are 
geared to creating steadily greater supranational features in 
the commonwealth and removing unjustified barriers to economic 
and cultural ties. This was stated by Sergey Filatov, head of 
the Russian Federation president's administration, at the 
opening of an international conference on "Legal problems and 
information aspects of creating a single economic space within 
the CIS." 
  The main aim of the forum which opened today is to 
standardize legislation in the independent states of the former 
USSR to the greatest degree possible, in order to create a 
single economic space within the CIS, but without harming their 
individual sovereignty in any way. The conference is being 
attended by delegations from all the commonwealth member states, 
the Baltic states and representatives of the European Community. 
  Vladimir Shumeyko, Chairman of the Interparliamentary 
Assembly of the CIS Member Countries, is taking part in its work. 
  Russian President Boris Yeltsin and Prime Minister Viktor 
Chernomyrdin have sent greetings to the conference, which will 
last two days. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

