<H3> <TI>   Grachev, ROK Defense Minister Discuss Cooperation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Grachev, ROK Defense Minister Discuss Cooperation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2904084694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0714 
GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2904084694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondents Nikolay </F>
Geronin and Mikhail Shevtsov] 
  [Text] Moscow, 29 Apr -- "The visit by Russian President 
Boris Yeltsin to the Republic of Korea in 1992 marked the start 
of our relations," Russian Defense Minister Pavel Grachev said, 
opening talks with Yi Pyong-tae, ROK national defense minister, 
who is in Russia on an official visit. "We are offering South 
Korea cooperation in various fields, including the military." 
  Yi Pyong-tae, for his part, noted that, during the flight 
from Tokyo to Moscow, the South Korean delegation "crossed the 
huge territory of Russia and we sensed the great potential of 
your country." 
  As already reported, the defense ministers of Russia and the 
ROK are exchanging views on the development of the situation in 
Northeast Asia and, primarily, on the issue of the 
nonproliferation of nuclear weapons in the Korean peninsula. P. 
Grachev and Yi Pyong-tae will discuss ways of expanding 
Russian-South Korean military cooperation. A document on mutual 
understanding over measures to develop ties between the Defense 
Ministries of Russia and the ROK in 1994-95 is expected to be 
signed. 
  During his stay in Russia, the head of the South Korean 
defense department will also meet high-ranking representatives 
of the Russian Government and will visit miltary units and 
defense enterprises. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

