<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Discussion Continues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Discussion Continues </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2904102194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0830 
GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2904102194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At the end of today's talks, Pavel Grachev and Yi 
Pyong-tae signed a memorandum on mutual understanding between 
the Defense Ministries of Russia and the Republic of Korea and a 
declaration on military cooperation between the two countries. 
In the words of Russian Defense Minister, these documents 
reflect the sides' intention to develop broader cooperation and 
determine the main events within the framework of ties between 
the two countries' military departments in 1994-95. 
  Pavel Grachev told journalists after the documents were 
signed that he had received an invitation from his South Korean 
counterpart to visit the Republic of Korea in 1995. We hope, 
said the Russian defense minister, to sign additional documents 
there on closer cooperation, perhaps in the military-technical 
sphere. He did not rule out the possibility of an agreement on 
preventing various kinds of unauthorized military actions being 
signed in Seoul. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

