<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Returns to Moscow, Reports on Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev Returns to Moscow, Reports on Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2804204794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1950 
GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2804204794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Dmitriy </F>
Gorokhov] 
  [Text] Moscow, 28 Apr--A ministerial level meeting 
involving Russia, the United States, the European Union [EU], 
and the United Nations to discuss matters regarding a Bosnian 
settlement could be held as early as the beginning of May. This 
was stated by Andrey Kozyrev on Thursday [28 April] evening upon 
his return to Moscow from his trip to Geneva and Bonn, where he 
had talks with the leaders of the foreign policy departments of 
the United States, France, and Germany. 
  "There is a fairly big chance that success will be achieved 
in organizing a ministerial meeting during the course of next 
week," the Russian foreign minister told journalists. He said 
that a possible venue for the meeting was Geneva. 
  According to Kozyrev, much will depend on how things go in 
the contact group of four that has been established at the level 
of special representatives to prepare a full report on the 
situation in Bosnia-Herzegovina. It has emerged that Russian 
Deputy Foreign Minister Vitaliy Churkin, who represents Russia 
in the group, will have a meeting in Oslo within the next few 
days with Thorvald Stoltenberg, the cochairman of the 
coordinating committee of the International Conference on 
Yugoslavia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-17969 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov083_a_94011" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-083 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  29 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Calls for Military Cooperation With ROK </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev Calls for Military Cooperation With ROK </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2904102694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0840 
GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2904102694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Anatoliy Krasnov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 29 Apr (ITAR-TASS) -- Relations between 
Russia and South Korea are definitely improving, Russian Foreign 
Minister Andrey Kozyrev said at a meeting today with South 
Korean National Defense Minister Yi Pyong-tae, here on an 
official visit. I am pleased that the military component in 
these relations has a worthy place, the head of Russian 
diplomacy said. Not only do we no longer look at each other 
along the barrel of a gun, we are ready to cooperate in setting 
up these relations for the joint security of friendly states and 
to have full-scale military cooperation, A. Kozyrev stressed. 
  During the meeting, the ministers intend to discuss the 
situation on the Korean peninsula along with other international 
problems and questions of mutual relations. 

</TEXT>

