<H3> <TI>   Russian, Azeri Parliaments Sign Cooperation Deal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian, Azeri Parliaments Sign Cooperation Deal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2804173694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1454 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2804173694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Viktor Shulman] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 28 TASS -- Russian Federation Council 
Chairman Vladimir Shumeyko and visiting Azerbaijani Parliament 
Chairman Rasul Guliyev signed an agreement on 
inter-parliamentary cooperation between the Russian Federal 
Assembly and the Azerbaijani Supreme Soviet in Moscow on 
Thursday. 
  The agreement comes into force as of the day it is signed. 
  The sides pledged to promote all forms of 
inter-parliamentary 
cooperation in order to establish a legal basis for the 
development of relations in all spheres of mutual interest. 
They also agreed to set up a standing inter-parliamentary 
commission to coordinate interaction. 
  The commission will aim at promoting the development of 
state 
relations between the Russian Federation and Azerbaijan. It 
will hold sessions at least twice a year in Moscow and Baku. 

</TEXT>

