<H3> <TI>   Russia Presses for Ratification of Baykonur Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia Presses for Ratification of Baykonur Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2804175294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1525 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2804175294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Diplomatic Panorama" feature: Reports by </F>
Diplomatic Correspondents Igor Porshnev, Vitaly Trubetskoy, and 
others] 
  [Text] In the near term Russia should ratify the agreement 
on the leasing of the Baykonur cosmodrome signed with 
Kazakhstan. Early May the Russian Space Agency (RSA) and the 
Russian Foreign Ministry intend to prepare all the necessary 
documents related to the agreement on the leasing of the 
cosmodrome so that Russian President Boris Yeltsin would present 
them to the State Duma for consideration. A top-ranking 
employee of the RSA reported to Interfax that the text of 
Yeltsin's letter which explains the need to ratify the agreement 
as soon as possible should be prepared by Friday. 
  The RSA representative underlined that "the presidents' 
signatures dated March 28 are not enough to hand over the 
cosmodrome for lease." "The sum totalling 115 million dollars 
(for the lease) is a large amount money and the decision on its 
allocation should be included into the budget of the Russian 
Federation," stressed he. "If this does not take place Russia 
will remain without Baykonur," he said. 

</TEXT>

