<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Publishing of Lead Papers To Be Halted 29 Apr </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Publishing of Lead Papers To Be Halted 29 Apr </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2804144494 Minsk BELAPAN in Belarusian 1240 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2804144494 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk BELAPAN </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today, a number of Belarusian newspapers have 
published an open letter to the readers signed by the chief 
editors of such leading Belarusian newspapers as NARODNAYA 
GAZETA, ZVYAZDA, and SOVETSKAYA BELORUSSIYA. "The Belarusian 
press is on the brink of disaster," the letter reads. 
"Expenditures for publishing a large-circulation newspaper 
amount to 1 billion [not further specified] a week. Funds 
coming from subscription fees will be enough for the next few 
days. ...Neither advertisement nor other forms of commercial 
operations, with which editorial boards have been forced to 
deal, will ensure further existence of the press." Beginning 29 
April, as the letter points out, publication of newspapers will 
be halted, except for the 1 and 9 May issues which will be 
devoted to Victory Day. "Although this is not a strike," the 
authors note, "there are grounds to hold one. ...The editorial 
boards are ready to resume publishing as soon as a solution to 
the current deadlock is found." 

</TEXT>

