<H3> <TI>   Delegation Fails To Leave for NATO Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Delegation Fails To Leave for NATO Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2904081494 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 2018 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2904081494 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau BASAPRESS, 26/4/1994 -- The military 
delegation of the Republic of Moldova, which had been invited to 
today's reunion of the heads of major general staffs of NATO 
countries and partner states, did not leave for Brussels, 
announced to BASA informed sources from the Minister of Defence 
(MD) from Chisinau. Anatol Cosciug, the chief of the military 
policy and treaties section of the MD of Moldova, said that the 
fact that the Moldovan delegation did not attend the reunion in 
Brussels is not connected with the refusal of Russia to sign the 
"Partnership for Peace" NATO program. Cosciug, excluding any 
political aspect, indicated that the Embassy of Belgium in 
Moscow didn't manage to issue the necessary visas. The Moldovan 
delegation was to be headed by Pavel Chirau, the chief of the 
General Staff of the Military Forces of Moldova. 

</TEXT>

