<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ambassador to Moscow Resigns </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2904083994 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 2018 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2904083994 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau BASAPRESS, 26/4/1994 -- Yesterday the 
ambassador of the Republic of Moldova in Moscow, Anatol Taran, 
submitted his resignation. Taran declared to BASA that until 
President Mircea Snegur signs the order accepting his 
resignation, diplomatic ethics do not allow him to present 
details concerning the reasons of his request. Asked if he was 
sure that Snegur will accept his resignation, Taran said it was 
highly probable; in case of rejection he intends to insist upon 
acceptance. According to Taran, after the Easter holidays, 
during which he intends to visit to take his leave of the 
president, government and colleagues from the diplomatic corps 
accredited in the Russian Federation; he will then return to 
Chisinau. Informed sources from Chisinau announced to BASA that 
a possible candidate for the resigned post would be Grigore 
Eremei, current ambassador of the Republic of Moldova in Minsk. 

