transition to a market economy, mentioning the stability of the 
national currency and reduction of inflation. According to 
Snegur, Moldova's foreign policy will be founded on certain laws 
that will be examined and adopted in the near future. He said 
that "the present Parliament that has a majority faction 
displays constructivity in its activity. It is very likely to 
eliminate the conflicts in Eastern and Southern Moldova," said 
Snegur. Both Snegur and Faruq Mustafa `Ali pointed out that the 
economic relations between the two states can be developed, 
particularly in agriculture. 

