<H3> <TI>   President Praises Border Accord With China </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Praises Border Accord With China </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2804151094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1018 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2804151094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A border demarcation agreement between Kazakhstan 
and China crowns their bilateral ties, Kazakh President 
Nursultan Nazarbayev declared at farewell ceremony for the 
Chinese Premier Li Peng in Alma Ata [Almaty] Thursday [28 April]. 
  "Not a single former USSR state, including Russia, has 
legally demarcated frontiers with China," Nazarbayev stressed. 
  In his opinion, the bilateral accords on transport give 
Kazakhstan access to all Chinese provinces and to Central Asia. 
He spoke highly of his talks with Li Peng on global issues, on 
the situation in CIS, and on Kazakh-Chinese relations. 
  He called fruitful the exchange of reform-making experience, 
which has, as he put it, an Asian flavor. Nazarbayev was 
pleased with Li Peng's support of his initiatives to build up 
trust and set up a common market in Asia. 

</TEXT>

