<F P=100> Turkmenistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   French Official Comments on Bosnian Settlement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    French Official Comments on Bosnian Settlement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2904021294 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1606 
GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2904021294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS special correspondents Lyudmila Glazovskaya </F>
and Mikhail Kalmykov] 
  [Text] Ashkhabad [Ashgabat], 28 Apr -- All influential 
forces concerned about the Bosnian crisis -- the United States, 
Russia, the European Union, and the United Nations -- should 
work together to propose a general plan for a peaceful 
settlement to the conflicting sides, Alain Lamassoure, the 
French minister delegate for European affairs, said here today. 
Answering a question from an ITAR-TASS correspondent on the 
prospects for a Bosnian settlement, he expressed satisfaction 
with the fact that a kind of contact group has already been set 
up at the level of experts. "France is in favor of convening a 
meeting of representatives of the European Union, Russia, and 
the United States with the participation of the United Nations." 
Such a course should enable progress to be made in the search 
for ways to a peaceful settlement in Bosnia, he believes. 
  Some aspects of the Bosnian crisis were touched upon at 
talks 
between official delegations and expert groups from France and 
Turkmenistan within the framework of Francois Mitterrand's 
working visit to Ashkhabad, which ended today. The French side 
set out its approach to the Bosnia problem and expressed regret 
in connection with the fact that Foreign Minister Alain Juppe 
had not come to Turkmenistan. He was unable to leave Europe 
because French diplomacy is currently undertaking active efforts 
in the Bosnian sphere. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

