<H3> <TI>   Karabakh Officials Claim Cease-Fire Not Observed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Karabakh Officials Claim Cease-Fire Not Observed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2904085994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0758 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2904085994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tigran Liloyan] </F>
  [Text] Yerevan April 29 TASS -- A ceasefire in the zone of 
the Karabakh conflict is not observed, ITAR-TASS learnt here on 
Friday from Manvel Sarkisyan, adviser of the Nagorno-Karabakh 
foreign minister. 
  He noted that the Karabakh side agreed on Thursday [28 
April] 
to cease fire during the last night, provided the mediator -- 
the Russian Federation -- receives a similar reply from the 
opposing side -- Azerbaijan. 
  In the meantime, there was no confirmation of such a reply, 
Sarkisyan said. Besides, the diplomat stressed, the Azeri side 
massed combat materiel and weapons near the north-eastern border 
of Nagorno-Karabakh and was regularly shelling the Mardakertskiy 
district from artillery during the last night and this morning. 
  Despite the cloudy weather, the situation is very tense at 
that section of the front, noted the adviser representing his 
ministry in Armenia. 

</TEXT>

