<H3> <TI>   Border Villages Fired on From Azerbaijan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Border Villages Fired on From Azerbaijan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2904103394 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0831 
GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2904103394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tigran Liloyan] </F>
  [Text] Yerevan, 29 Apr (ITAR-TASS) -- From 1700 on Thursday 
until late at night, Azerbaijani units periodically shelled the 
Armenian border villages of Vagan in Krasnoselskiy rayon, 
Chinari in Taushskiy rayon, and Sevkar and Berkaber in 
Idzhevanskiy rayon using all types of weapons. The ITAR-TASS 
correspondent learned this today from the Armenian defense 
ministry's press center. 
  According to the same source, at the same time, on Thursday 
evening, the border village of Shagat in Sisianskiy rayon in the 
southeast of the republic came under howitzer and automatic fire 
from the territory of the Nakhichevan Autonomous Republic. 
  In all cases, the Armenian side did not return fire and 
there 
were no casualties, the Armenian Ministry of Defense stressed. 

</TEXT>

