<H3> <TI>   Edict on Elimination of Chernobyl Consequences </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Edict on Elimination of Chernobyl Consequences </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2804152094 Kiev HOLOS UKRAYINY in Ukrainian 23 Apr 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU2804152094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev HOLOS UKRAYINY </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Ukrainian Presidential Directive on Urgent Measures for </F>
Eliminating the Consequences of the Chernobyl Catastrophe in 
Kiev Oblast's Polissya Rayon" issued in Kiev on 22 Apr] 
  [Text] 1. Ukraine's Cabinet of Ministers must see to it 
that, until 1 September 1995, residents be evacuated from the 
populated areas of Kiev Oblast's Polissya Rayon that are 
categorized as zones of unquestionable (mandatory) evacuation. 
To do so, it is necessary, by 1 May 1994, to find a possibility 
for allocating additional capital amounting to 1 trillion 
karbovantsi from the Fund For Carrying Out Measures on 
Eliminating the Consequences of the Chernobyl Catastrophe and 
Social Protection of the Population in 1994 to the Kiev Oblast 
State Administration for building housing; 
  --with the participation of the Kiev Oblast State 
Administration, to take urgent measures for a radical 
improvement of the material and technological provision of 
medical and educational institutions and for establishing 
telephone communications and vehicle traffic between the 
populated areas of Polissya Rayon and Kiev; 
  --to elaborate and adopt, by 1 July 1994, a separate program 
for eliminating the consequences of the Chernobyl catastrophe in 
the populated areas of Polissya Rayon from which residents are 
not evacuated; 
  --to submit, by 1 July 1994, for the consideration of 
Ukraine's Supreme Council, proposals on the creation of a single 
body for managing exclusion zones and for unquestionable 
(mandatory) evacuation, as well as on placing those citizens who 
had, on the day of the accident, permanently resided and 
continue to reside and work in populated areas situated in the 
zone of unquestionable (mandatory) evacuation, into category two 
of the participants in the liquidation of the accident at the 
Chernobyl Nuclear Electric Power Station [AES]. 
  2. Ukraine's Ministry for Issues of Protection of the 
Population from the Consequences of the Accident at the 
Chernobyl AES, with the participation of Ukraine's Academy of 
Sciences, Ukraine's Ministry of Agriculture and Foodstuffs, and 
the Kiev Oblast State Administration, must submit, by 1 July 
1994, for the consideration of Ukraine's Cabinet of Ministers 
the following: --proposals on the procedure of using land 
in Polissya Rayon, proceeding from the intensity of radioactive 
contamination, the fertility of the soils, the demographic 
situation, and the production costs and demand for the rayon's 
produce; 
  --on the expedience of preserving and maintaining buildings 
and structures, as well as on the further utilization of land in 
the exclusion zone. 
  3. To draw the attention of Ukraine's Minister of 
Agriculture 
and Foodstuffs Yu. Karasyk to the unsatisfactory fulfillment of 
Article 6 of Ukrainian Presidential Edict No. 348 of 21 August 
1993 "On Additional Measures Regarding the Elimination of the 
Consequences of the Chernobyl Catastrophe" in what concerns the 
organization and control over the supply of clean foodstuffs to 
those zones that have been affected by the catastrophe at the 
Chernobyl AES and to oblige him to eradicate the existing 
shortcomings as soon as possible. 
  4. The State Control and Auditing Service at Ukraine's 
Ministry of Finance and Ukraine's Ministry of Internal Affairs 
must, by 15 June 1994, carry out an inspection of the 
utilization in 1992-94 of the funds that were allocated for the 
liquidation of the consequences of the Chernobyl catastrophe and 
submit the materials of the inspection to the Ukrainian 
Presidential Administration. 
  Ukrainian President L. Kravchuk 
  Kiev, 22 April 1994 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

