<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Aliyev Speaks After Receiving CSCE Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Aliyev Speaks After Receiving CSCE Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2904141994 Baku TURAN in English 1012 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2904141994 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baku (April 28) TURAN -- "We welcome the stepped-up 
activity of the CSCE Minsk Group and all the efforts you have 
made in the past. We would like to see your work succeed", said 
President Aliyev during his meeting with the CSCE Minsk Group 
delegation headed by Mathias Mosberg. 
  According to Geydar Aliyev, Baku is striving for cease-fire 
and is seeking ways to establish peace in the region and it is 
in connection with this that the Chairman of the Milli Majlis, 
Rasul Guliyev, is actively negotiating with Moscow. 
  "After the meeting with Rasul Guliyev, Russian Defense 
Minister, Pavel Grachev, said that he will take measures to 
cease hostilities on April 28 at midnight, but Armenia continues 
to attack", said President Aliyev. 
  Azeri President mentioned that the peacemaking mission of 
the 
CSCE Minsk Group will lead to no effect without a cease-fire. 
The leader of the delegation, Deputy Chairman of the Minsk 
Group, Mathias Mosberg, agreed with this point of view. 
  "A cease-fire is the key element to the settlement of this 
problem. The aim of our visit to the region is to achieve a 
truce and we will make every effort to bring that about", 
stressed Mosberg. 
  Today, the delegation is scheduled to visit the war zone and 
then will return to Baku. After that the delegation again will 
visit Khankendi [Stepanakert] and Yerevan. 

</TEXT>

