<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   CSCE Delegation Comes Under Armenian Fire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CSCE Delegation Comes Under Armenian Fire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2804195794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1928 
GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2804195794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Sevindzh Abdulayev] </F>
  [Text] Baku, 28 Apr--This evening (at about 1800 hours 
local time) a delegation of the CSCE Minsk group on Nagornyy 
Karabakh [Nagorno-Karabakh] was fired upon by Armenian armed 
formations at Terter, in the center of Terterskiy Rayon in the 
southwest of Azerbaijan. 
  After arriving in Azerbaijan two days ago, the delegation 
went this afternoon to this frontline rayon to acquaint itself 
with the situation on the spot and to study the possibility of 
deploying CSCE observers there. 
  According to a confidential source, two missiles from a Grad 
launcher fell close to the building housing the local 
administration at the time when the CSCE representatives were 
there. According to preliminary information, there are no 
casualties. 

</TEXT>

