  [Text] Recently appointed Georgian Defense Minister Varden 
Nadabaidze has issued a number of appointment orders, the 
Ministry's press center told Interfax. 
  Major General Paata Datuashvili was relieved of his duties 
as 
first deputy defense minister to be replaced by Major General 
Guram Nikolaishvili who had been chief of the Georgian Army's 
General Staff. 
  Major General Nadar Tatarashvili was appointed as the chief 
of the general staff. Until recently, he was in charge of the 
Georgian peacekeeping forces in South Ossetia. 

