reports that President Boris Yeltsin was dissatisfied with his 
yesterday's meeting with intelligence chiefs. 
  In an interview with ITAR-TASS on Thursday, Baturin said 
that 
the meeting was held in a candid atmosphere and helped expose 
many problems and set new tasks. The president was satisfied 
with the meeting, he added. 

