<H3> <TI>   Counterintelligence Public Relations Center To Move </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Counterintelligence Public Relations Center To Move </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK2804124094 Moscow KURANTY in Russian 28 Apr 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> MK2804124094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KURANTY </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Viktor Mironov report: "Lubyanka Opens New Doors"] </F>
  [Text] The Public Relations Center of the Federal 
Counterintelligence Service [FCS] is going to move to a new 
office, although within the same well-known building the service 
inherited from the NKVD-KGB-Security Ministry. The move has 
been prompted by an increase in the press group personnel and, 
therefore, the need to improve their working conditions. The 
specific location of the center's new office has not been 
disclosed yet, but it is known that its staffers will have 
spacious rooms and a separate entrance, something that will ease 
access to the bulwark of counterintelligence for journalists and 
other interested citizens. To whom it may concern: the center's 
telephone numbers will not change. 

</TEXT>

