<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Militia Chief Reports Holiday Public Order Measures </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Militia Chief Reports Holiday Public Order Measures </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2804215194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1125 
GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2804215194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Crime Press correspondent Larisa Kislinskaya] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 28 Apr--The forces maintaining public order 
over the Easter and 1 May holidays will be increased 
considerably, Militia Lieutenant General Vyacheslav Ogorodnikov, 
head of the chief directorate for the maintenance of public 
order of Russia's Ministry of Internal Affairs, told a Crime 
Press correspondent. 
  Reinforced detachments will be posted around cemeteries and 
churches where services and religious processions are to be 
held. Measures for maintaining public order will be in operation 
outside churches until six a.m., the finishing time for the 
religious processions. 
  Reinforced posts will be mounted on 1 May at sites of mass 
public demonstrations, rallies, and marches. According to our 
information, these include Triumphal Square, Tverskaya Street, 
Manezhnaya and Kaluzhkaya Squares, and the University Metro 
station area. 
  As Ogorodnikov emphasized, the maintenance of public order 
will be implemented entirely by Moscow militia forces. Ministry 
of Internal Affairs troops are only being kept in reserve should 
unforeseen circumstances arise. 

</TEXT>

