<H3> <TI>   Chernomyrdin Seeks Funds Advance to Textile Industry </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chernomyrdin Seeks Funds Advance to Textile Industry </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2804164594 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> PM2804164594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Untitled POSTFACTUM report from the "Events of the Week" </F>
roundup -- from the FINANSOVYYE IZVESTIYA section page I] 
  [Text] Textile and light industry enterprises are hoping 
for a budget advance of 400 billion rubles [R]. Following the 
recent meeting between Premier Viktor Chernomyrdin and Tatyana 
Sosninaya, chairman of the Textile and Light Industry Union, a 
letter signed by Viktor Chernomyrdin and proposing "by way of an 
exception to resolve in a favorable manner the question of 
offering textile and light industry enterprises a budget advance 
of R400 billion, issued in stages as of May 1994, for the 
purchase of raw materials" was sent to the Russian Ministry of 
Finance. Apart from this, it is recommended that "the 
examination and signing of a sector wage agreement be speeded 
up." According to Tatyana Sosninaya, a wage agreement may be 
signed before 26 April. In which case, the obstacles preventing 
the signing of the Treaty on Social Accord by the textile 
workers' union will be removed. 

</TEXT>

