<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS freelance corrrespondent Semen Ivanov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 28 Apr -- Today at 2014 the Russian military 
space forces launched a space vehicle, Cosmos-2280, from launch 
pad number 31 at Baykonur space center. 
  The satellite was launched using a three-stage Soyuz-V 
launching vehicle. 
  An ITAR-TASS correspondent learned from the military space 
forces press center that the launch, which was carried out in 
the interests of the Russian Defense Ministry, took place 
successfully. 

</TEXT>

