<H3> <TI>   TASS Provides Parameters for Cosmos-2280 </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    TASS Provides Parameters for Cosmos-2280 </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2904083294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0721 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2904083294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Flight Control Centre (Moscow Region) April 29 TASS 
-- The Cosmos-2280 satellite was put into orbit with a Soyuz 
booster from the Baykonur Cosmodrome on April 28, 1994. The 
satellite will be used in the interests of the Russian Defence 
Ministry. 
  The satellite was put into orbit with the following 
parameters: 
  initial period of revolution -- 89 minutes, 
  apogee -- 290 kilometers, 
  perigee -- 198 kilometers, 
  orbital inclination -- 70 decrees. 
  The satellite's onboard equipment functions normally. 

</TEXT>

