<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military &amp; Space Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   TASS Reports on Mir Space Station Mission </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    TASS Reports on Mir Space Station Mission </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2904082794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0721 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2904082794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Flight Control Centre (Moscow Region) April 29 TASS 
- Another space week is nearing completion for Viktor Afanasyev, 
Yuriy Usachev and Valeriy Polyakov aboard the Mir space station. 
  The flight programme for the last two days included 
geophysical and astrophysical investigations as well as routine 
servicing of some systems of the station and modules. 
  Using videospectrometric equipment installed on the 
stabilised platform of the Kvant-2 module, the cosmonauts made 
several snapshots of the Earth's surface. The main tasks of 
this work were investigations of the ecological situation in 
major industrial hubs and areas of oil and gas production. 
  To study further mechanisms of generation of elementary 
high- 
energy charged particles in the earth's radiation belts and 
near- earch space, the crew fulfilled several experiments with 
the use of a magnetic spectrometer. 
  Under a medical checkup plan, the ship commander and flight 
engineer will undergo an echographic investigation of the 
cardiovascular system on Friday under the supervision of the 
crew doctor. 
  The station's flight continues under a preset programme. The 
cosmonauts are healthy and feel well. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

