<H3> <TI>   SPD's Vogel Calls For Investigating Schoenhuber </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SPD's Vogel Calls For Investigating Schoenhuber </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2903085394 Hamburg DPA in German 0746 GMT 29 Mar 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2903085394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hamburg (DPA) -- Former Social Democratic Party of 
Germany [SPD] Chairman Hans-Jochen Vogel has also come out in 
favor of criminal investigations against Franz Schoenhuber, 
chairman of the right-wing extremist Republikaner. Following 
his statements about Ignatz Bubis, chairman of the Central 
Council of Jews in Germany, the Munich public prosecutor's 
office must examine whether or not Schoenhuber committed the 
crime of incitement. The statements by the former television 
journalist are "indeed apt to disturb public peace," Vogel said 
in an interview on Saarland Radio on Thursday [24 March]. 
  Yesterday SPD Deputy Chairwoman Herta Daeubler-Gmelin and 
Christian Democratic Union Secretary General Peter Hintze 
demanded criminal sanctions. Leading Free Democratic Party of 
Germany politicians were outraged about Schoenhuber's "shameless 
language and insulting comments." The right-wing extremist had 
accused Bubis of "instigating people," because Bubis had said 
that right-wing extremists were the "intellectual arsonists" of 
the attack on the synagogue in Luebeck. Even though Bubis does 
not want to file a complaint against Schoenhuber, if 
investigations are carried out for the crime of incitement, as 
Vogel demands, the public prosecutor's office could act even 
without a formal complaint. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

