<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Germany </F>
<H3> <TI>   Schoenhuber Maintains Accusations Against Bubis </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Schoenhuber Maintains Accusations Against Bubis </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2903111194 Hamburg DPA in German 0935 GMT 29 Mar 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2903111194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- Franz Schoenhuber, chairman of the 
right-wing extremist Republikaner, maintains his accusation of 
"instigating people" against Ignatz Bubis, chairman of the 
Central council of Jews. "I do not retract one word here and 
now," Schoenhuber stated in Bonn on Tuesday [29 March] and 
added, "I am calmly expecting a lawsuit." 
  Schoenhuber justified his accusations by pointing to 
statements by Bubis at the beginning of March, when the latter, 
in the view of the Republikaner chairman, blamed followers of 
his party for being coresponsible for arson attacks. As a 
result, Schoenhuber filed a criminal complaint with the Bonn 
Land Court on 4 March, accusing Bubis of instigating people and 
slander. The proceedings are underway but it was passed on to 
the Mainz public prosecutor's office, obviously because of 
competence. 
  After the attack on the synagogue in Luebeck Schoenhuber had 
repeated the accusation and called Bubis one "of the worst 
instigators of people in Germany," after Bubis, for his part, 
had called right-wing extremist parties "intellectual arsonists" 
and blamed them for the attack on the synagogue. 

</TEXT>

