<F P=103> AU3003160794 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Munich -- The Landshut Public Prosecutor's Office 
has initiated preliminary investigations against Republikaner 
Chairman Franz Schoenhuber for slandering Ignatz Bubis, chairman 
of the Central Council of Jews in Germany. A decision as to 
whether there is sufficient reason for initiating investigations 
cannot be expected before Easter, Senior Public Prosecutor 
Bernhard Brenneis told DPA on Tuesday [29 March]. 
  Before investigations are started, the European Parliament 
will have to lift Schoenhuber's immunity. Schoenhuber's 
accusation of "instigation" against Bubis has been met with 
dismay from all parties. 

