<F P=102>   BR2803133994 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1803 GMT 25 
Mar 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR2803133994 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "China/Italy: Export Credit Granted"] </F>
  [Text] (ANSA) Beijing, March 25 -- An export credit line 
worth 75 million dollars has been granted to the Industrial and 
Commercial Bank of China by a group of Italian banks led by 
Crediop, part of the San Paolo di Torino group. 
  The credit line is part of a 300 million dollar financing 
operation for Chinese purchases of European tools and 
technology, aimed at enhancing Sino-Italian trade which last 
year more than doubled. 
  A first tranche of 150 million dollars went to the Bank of 
China, and the second, of 75 milion dollars, went to the 
People's Construction Bank. 

</TEXT>

