<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Applicants Agree to Vote Compromise, Conclude EU Negotaitions </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Austria Says Compromise `Common Sense' </H4>

<F P=102> AU3103134594 Vienna DIE PRESSE in German 31 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU3103134594 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna DIE PRESSE </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["laho"-signed report: "Talks With European Union </F>
Concluded"] 
  [Text] Brussels -- The accession talks of the European 
Union [EU] with Austria, Sweden, Finland, and Norway were 
concluded on Wednesday evening [30 March] when the last open 
chapter on institutions was settled. An improvement for Austria 
was achieved regarding its representation in the EU bodies. It 
will be allowed to send 21 (instead of 20) deputies to the 
European Parliament, and 12 each (instead of 11) to the Economic 
and Social Committee and the Committee of the Regions. 
Austria's ambassador to the European Union, Manfred Scheich, 
stressed that the compromise on the blocking minority in the EU 
Council of Ministers adopted earlier is the "result of political 
common sense." 

</TEXT>

