<H4>    Sweden Agrees to Council, EP Votes </H4>

<F P=102> LD3003203694 Stockholm Radio Sweden in Swedish 2000 GMT 30 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3003203694 </F>
<F P=104>  Stockholm Radio Sweden </F>
<F P=105>  Swedish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sweden's negotiations on membership of the European 
Union [EU] have now definitely been concluded. In the Council 
of Ministers, the highest decision-making body in the EU, Sweden 
will get four votes; Sweden had asked for five votes in the 
negotiations. In the European Parliament Sweden will have 22 
votes. If the result of the national referendum is "yes" in 
November, Sweden can become a member of the EU on 1 January 1995. 

</TEXT>

