<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Labor Ministry Reports Increase in Unemployment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Labor Ministry Reports Increase in Unemployment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3103084694 Paris AFP in English 0803 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU3103084694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Paris, March 31 (AFP) -- The number of people 
unemployed in France rose by 0.2 percent to a total of 3,312,000 
official seasonally-adjusted figures showed on Thursday [31 
March]. 
  In each of the three previous months the number of people 
unemployed had risen by 0.1 percent. In September the number 
had increased by 0.8 percent and in October by 1.2 percent. 
  The figures for February, which were published by the Labour 
Ministry, showed that the number of people unemployed continued 
to increase beyond the point of three million which was reached 
in January when it rose to 3,307,100. 
  The rate of unemployment, on the basis of a calculation used 
by the International Labour Organisation, remained steady at 
12.2 percent of the workforce. 
  Figures published by the official French INSEE statistical 
institute, which were also published on Thursday and which are 
based on an ILO calculation, showed that 3,061,000 people were 
unemployed in February compared with 3,055,000 in January and 
2,787,000 in February 1993, representing an increase of 274,000 
in 12 months. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

