<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   AGF Insurance Group Reports 35 Percent Profit Drop </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    AGF Insurance Group Reports 35 Percent Profit Drop </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3003154894 Paris AFP in English 1514 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU3003154894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Paris, March 30 (AFP) -- Major French insurance 
group AGF reported Wednesday [30 March] that it made a 
group-share consolidated net profit of 977 million francs (170 
million dollars) last year, down 35 percent from 1.49 billion 
francs in 1992. 
  New chairman Antoine Jeancourt-Galignani said that banking 
activities (losses of Comptoir des Entrepreneurs and of Banque 
du Phenix) had depressed the group result by 2.5 billion francs. 
  He said the goup's over-all result should improve this year. 

</TEXT>

