<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Confident of Forming Government </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Confident of Forming Government </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3003175994 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1702 GMT 
30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3003175994 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] "We will form a government and do so soon," Silvio 
Berlusconi said today, following his first [postelection] 
meeting with Umberto Bossi. Berlusconi said they will meet 
again on Friday [1 April], adding, "There is a very friendly 
climate. We are on the right road." 
  Bossi and Roberto Maroni also thought the meeting was "very 
positive." Bossi said: "We spoke, we started to thrash things 
out, and, if everything goes as it should, we will be able to 
give the country a government soon." 

</TEXT>

