<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   No Role in New Government </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    No Role in New Government </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3003195194 Paris AFP in English 1934 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU3003195194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Rome, March 30 (AFP) -- The leader of Italy's 
neo-fascist National Alliance Gianfranco Fini confirmed 
Wednesday [30 March] that he will not be a member of Italy's new 
government despite this week's landslide vote to a right-wing 
alliance. 
  Fini told reporters at a meeting of his movement that he had 
spoken to Forza Italia (Go Italy) party leader Silvio Berlusconi 
by telephone after the TV magnate met Northern League leader 
Umberto Bossi in Milan. Following that meeting, Berlusconi 
claimed the prime ministership, making it understood that Bossi 
no longer opposed his holding it. 
  The right-wing alliance of the Northern League, National 
Alliance and Forza Italia parties won a landslide victory in 
legislative elections on Sunday and Monday. Berlusconi and 
Bossi are due to meet again in Milan on Friday. 

</TEXT>

