<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ciller Refuses Resignation `Gesture' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ciller Refuses Resignation `Gesture' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC3103055794 Paris AFP in English 0230 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC3103055794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, March 31 (AFP)--Four Turkish ministers 
symbolically handed their resignation to Prime Minister Tansu 
Ciller late Wednesday [31 March] after failing to win election 
as mayors in municipal elections Sunday, a government source 
said. 
  In a statement, Ciller thanked the four, all members of her 
True Path Party, for their "gesture" but said she had no 
intention of reshuffling the cabinet at the moment. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-18147 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drweu062_q_94003" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-WEU-94-062 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  31 Mar 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ballots Found in Trabzon Dump; Protest Filed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ballots Found in Trabzon Dump; Protest Filed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA3103095294 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 0855 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA3103095294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Diyarbakir, Mar. 31 (A.A.) -- Social Democratic 
Populist Party (SHP) mayoral candidate Vahit Yigit and 
independent candidate Esref Tanriverdi filed a formal protest to 
the election board as great numbers of stamped ballots were 
found in a dump. 
  Yigit and Tanriverdi requested the nullification of the 
election. 
  Officials of the Motherland Party (ANAP) filed an official 
complaint because 6,000 ballots in the Black Sea city of Trabzon 
were found. As the local election board rejected the objection, 
ANAP officials said that they will apply to a higher board. 
  The candidate of fundamentalist Prosperity Party (RP) had 
won 
over the ANAP candidate with by narrow margin of 2,130 votes. 
  The former president of the high election board Orhan Aydin 
said, after reports on huge amounts of ballots in dumps and 
schools that the March 27 local elections might be canceled if 
the ballots found would change the result. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

