<H3> <TI>   Libyan Foreign Liaison Official Arrives in Ankara </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Libyan Foreign Liaison Official Arrives in Ankara </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA3103062794 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 2100 
GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA3103062794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] 'Umar al-Muntasir, Libyan secretary of the General 
People's Bureau for External Liaison and International 
Cooperation, arrived on an official visit in Ankara tonight. 
At Esenboga Airport the Libyan minister was received by 
Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin. In an airport statement, Cetin 
said that there are deep rooted relations based on friendship 
and brotherhood between the two countries. He added that 
measures needed to further develop relations in all fields will 
be discussed at the talks. Cetin said that Libya provides 
business opportunities to the Turkish private sector, adding 
that Turkish contractors have made significant contributions to 
Libya's development. 
  Al-Muntasir said that his visit will be beneficial in 
developing bilateral friendship and cooperation. Pointing out 
that his country attaches great importance to relations with 
Turkey, al-Muntasir added that bilateral and international 
problems will be discussed during his visit. The visit of 
al-Muntasir and the delegation accompanying him will last for 
three days. 

</TEXT>

