<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Finland </F>
<H3> <TI>   * VL Leader: EU Talks Behind Russian Moves </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    * VL Leader: EU Talks Behind Russian Moves </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94P20564A Helsinki HUFVUDSTADSBLADET in Swedish 14 Mar 94 p 7 </F>
<F P=103> 94P20564A </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki HUFVUDSTADSBLADET </F>
<F P=105>  Swedish </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Finnish News Agency report: "Freedom From Alliances in the </F>
Shade"] 
  [Text] Claes Andersson, Left Alliance [VL] Chairman, is 
attacking Finland's foreign policy leadership for not having 
acted with sufficient determination in the EU [European Union] 
negotiations to keep the country out of military alliances. In 
Helsinki on Saturday [12 March], Andersson asserted that the 
country's striving for freedom from alliances had been mentioned 
when Finland first applied for EU membership. 
  "An attempt has been made to conceal the freedom from 
alliances [doctrine] in order not to jeopardize the membership 
talks," he said. 
  According to Andersson, the strengthening of Russian troops 
on Finland's eastern border is partly because Russia is 
preparing against a change in Finnish security policy in the 
event Finland becomes an EU member and that organization 
develops its own defense policy cooperation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

