<H3> <TI>   ELDYK Concludes Military Exercise `Successfully' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ELDYK Concludes Military Exercise `Successfully' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC3103112894 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 0900 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC3103112894 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The final phase of ELDYK's [Greek Forces in Cyprus] 
exercise TAMS EVAGORAS 94, which took place this morning in the 
area of Vizakia, concluded successfully and with the use of live 
ammunition. The exercise included an offensive and takeover of 
a hill that was occupied by the enemy. A platoon of National 
Guard LEONIDHAS tanks also participated in the exercise. 
  ELDYK Commander Colonel Evangelos Briasoulis expressed 
satisfaction with the exercise and added that ELDYK is always 
ready to carry out its mission. The exercise was observed by 
the Lt. Colonel Ioannis Fotiadhis, National Guard deputy 
commander, who expressed satisfaction and added that the 
exercise is an example to follow. 

