<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense, Interior, State Ministers Submit Resignations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense, Interior, State Ministers Submit Resignations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA3103054294 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 2100 
GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA3103054294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report] </F>
  [Text] Ministers of State Necmettin Cevheri and Bekir Sami 
Dace, National Defense Minister Mehmet Golhan, and Interior 
Minister Nahit Mentese have resigned. According to a statement 
issued by the Prime Ministry Press Center, the ministers 
submitted their resignations to Prime Minister Tansu Ciller. 
Assessing the election results in their letters of resignation, 
the ministers noted that the True Path Party has emerged 
victorious despite difficult conditions. The ministers added 
that they chose to resign to enable the prime minister to act 
freely in the event a change might be deemed necessary in the 
government. 
  In a statement she issued, Ciller said that a change in the 
government is not currently considered, adding that she views 
the resignation of the ministers as a postelection gesture. 

</TEXT>

